      "SummaryText": "RMP EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n                                                          MARION,IL  NH3- SITE\n\n\n1.  FACILITY ACCIDENTIAL RELEASE AND EMERGENCY POLICY.\n\nTHE MANAGEMENT AND EMPLOYEES OF SOUTHERN FS, INC  ARE COMMITTED TO THE PREVENTION OF ANY ACCIDENTIAL RELEASES OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA.  IF AN ACCIDENTIAL RELEASE SHOULD OCCUR, THE FACILITY IS PREPARED TO WORK WITH THE LOCAL FIRE DEP,ARTMENT, OR OTHER AUTHORITIES, TO MITIGATE ANY RELEASE AND MINIMIZE THE IMPACT OF THE RELEASE TO  PEOPLE AND THE ENVIRONMENT.\n.\n\n2 THE  PRIMARY ACTIVITY AT THE FACILITY WHICH IS LOCATED AT 1501 EAST DEYOUNG STREET MARION, IL, IS THE STORAGE AND BLENDING OF FERTILIZERS FOR SALE TO FARMERS.  ANHYDROUS AMMONIA IS RECEIVED, STORED, AND DISTRIBUTED FOR DIRECT APPLICATION  AS A CROP NUTRIENT.THE STORAGE AND HANDLING SYSTEM CONSIST OF ONE STORAGE TANK (12,000 GALLONS), LOADING RISERS, ASSOCIATED PLUMBING AND NURSE TANKS.  ACCESS TO THE SITE IS RESTRICTED TO AUTHORIZED FACILITY  EMPLOYEES, AUTHORIZED MGT PERSONNEL AND AUTHORIZED CONTRACTORS. \n\nTHE MAXIMUM QUANTITY OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA THAT CAN BE STORED WOULD BE 170,000 POUNDS. THIS INCLUDES ANHYDROUS AMMONIA THAT COULD BE STORED IN NURSE TANKS.\n\n\n\n3.  THE ACCIDENTIAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM.\n\nTHIS FACILITY COMPLIES WITH EPA'S   ACCIDENTIAL RELEASE PREVENTION RULE AND WITH ALL APPLICABLE STATE CODES AND REGULATIONS.  THIS FACILITY HAS IMPLEMENTED THE PROVISIONS OF \" SAFETY REQUIREMENTS FOR THE STORAGE AND HANDLING OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA, K-61.1\", PUBLISHED BY THE AMERICAN STANDARDS  INSTITUTE, INC. AS ADOPTED BY THE STATE REGULATION AND THE STANDARDS OF THE U.S. OCCUPATIONAL SAFETY AND HEALTH ADMINISTRATION (OSHA), 29 CFR 1910.111, \"STORAGE AND HANDLING OF ANHYDROUS AMMONIA\".  COMPLIANCE WITH THESE REGULATIONS AND ON-GOING TRAINING OF OUR EMPLOYEES MAKE UP OUR ACCIDENTIAL RELEASE PREVENTION PROGRAM.\n\n\n4.  FIVE YEAR ACCIDENT HISTORY.\n\nON MAY 30, 2000 AN AREA FARMER ACCIDENTIALLY RELEASED A"
    },
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 1,
      "FacilityID": 31236,
      "SummaryText": "NURSE TANK FULL OF ANHYDROUS WHILE SIDE DRESSING  A CORN FIELD.  THE FARMER OVER TURNED HIS TOOL BAR WHILE GOING THRU A DITCH AND THE AMMONIA ESCAPED INTO THE ATMOSPHERE THRU THE TOOL BAR KNIVES. APPROXIMATELY 4000LBS WERE RELEASED.  THE RESIDENTS OF AN ASSISTED LIVING  NURSING HOME WAS EVACUATED FOR PRECAUTION.  THE ILLINOIS DEPT OF AG INVESTIGATED THE RELEASE AND DETERMINED IS WAS OPERATOR ERROR.  \n\n\n5.   THE EMERGENCY RESPONSE PROGRAM.\n\n\nTHE FACILITY HAS:\n\n     A WRITTEN EMERGENCY ACTION PLAN, IN ACCORDANCE WITH OSHA STANDARD, 29 CFR 1910.38;\n\n     PROVIDED STATE AND LOCAL AUTHORITIES THE EMERGENCY PLANNING AND THE COMMUNITY\n     RIGHT-TO-KNOW INFORMATION AS REQUIRED UNDER SARA TITLE III   (EPCRA);\n\n     IN THE EVENT OF AN EMERGENCY INVOLVING ANHYDROUS AMMONIA, IT IS OUR POLICY TO NOTIFY THE WILLIAMSON COUNTY  AND MARION FIRE DEPT AND THE WILLIAMSON COUNTY LEPC.\n\n6.   PLANNED CHANGES TO IMPROVE SAFETY.\n\n     SAFETY IMPROVEMENT IS AN ON-GOING PROCESS AT THE FACILITY.  PERIODIC EVALUATIONS \n     ARE PERFORMED TO ASSESS THE MAINTENANCE OF SAFE CONDITIONS.  THERE ARE NO  \n     SPECIFIC SAFETY RECOMMENDATIONS FOR  IMPLEMENTATION AT THIS TIME."
    }
  ]
